      • saveInternals

        public StreamableOperatorInternals saveInternals()
        Create the internals calculated during execution that need to be merged and fed back to the node that controls the execution. Only distributed streamable operator should have internals (and only if they need to pass information to the node, e.g. parts of the output object or view internals or warning messages).
        Overrides:
        saveInternals in class StreamableOperator
        Returns:
        The internals that are transferred back to the client. Internals of different operators are merged using a MergeOperator.
